	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>the FT15 cap did come from a statement from VI, in it they said that at that time that two of the same FTs didn't stack (it was fixed 1-2 patches after the statement was made as was stated in the statement) also in the statement they said that the biggest FT on an item at the time was 5, so at the time the cap was 15.&nbsp;&nbsp;1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 = 15.  this number was outdated the week it came out by the statement it came out in.  i would be interested in knowing how a log could prove mana regeneration as no mana totals/ increases/ decreases/ etc. are noted in your log.  logs are further unreliable because of lvl 20-30 specilization, which makes the mana taken per spell random (if only by a small degree).  the only way i know how to test it is to sit down with a stopwatch and time how long it takes to go from OOM to FM with 15 FT and above 15 FT.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jul 11 03:18:17 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
