	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a shaman with torpor, a few extra hp/tick is useful, but not really vital. The same goes for ft items to be honest and even KEI is nice to have, but hardly your main source of mana. True with FT15 and KEI, if you can get them without sacrificing AC/HP, they are nice to have. 1 Malo and 1 Slow is 600 mana though on every mob, not counting frequent resists, and with a fast pull rate clear the way to a boss mob, you need to get mana faster than these offer.<br><br>Mana Comes from Canni 4 and later Canny 5, and for really high end shaman Canni 5 is very important to equipment choices.<br><br>Canni 5 is a massive hp to mana AAXP skill. It converts 1924 hp to 1200 mana.<br><br>If your HP pool is only around 2K self buffed or 3K cleric buffed, using it in many situations is suicidal.<br><br>If you can gain an extra 1khp from both STA and HP items, taking you up to 3K (self) and 4K (raid), the choices of when you can use Canni 5 increase dramatically.<br><br>In a solo situation, when on full hp, hit torpor and then canni5. In a raid situation, hiting canni 5 will not cause auto agro on you from low hp, so can be used when fighting non-AE mobs, and maybe with torpor running with AE mobs as well if timed right.<br><br>This neck items offers 12 STA (36 hp) and 75 hp, 111 hp in total. Add to it some rings or earings from CT, a Vindi BP etc, and you will get your 4K hp raid buffed, hopefully more.<br>The AC is useful, when I surpassed 1100 AC in normal exp grps, the damage I took compared to when I was at 1030AC was significantly reduced. <br>1250AC is currently my goal, with 4500 HP raid buffed ;)<br><br>Sordain 60 shaman AB server<br><br><br><br>Name: Cannibalization <br>Pre-Requisite(s) Mental Clarity <br>Level Requirement: 59 <br>Ability Type: Activated&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Re-Use Time: 3 minutes <br>Max Training: 1 Levels <br>Point Cost: 5 <br>Description: This ability takes a massive amount of life from the Shaman and replenshishes their mana. <br>It takes 1924 hitpoints from the Shaman to give them 1200 mana back.<br><br>It can be re-used every 69 seconds, but must be used in relatively safe circumstances.<br> <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Shaman of the T<br>Wolves of the Tundra<br>Saryrn</td></tr>
